Center: IAEA Nuclear Data Section, Vienna, Austria
title: Proton Scattering from 27Al in the Energy Range from 3.5 to 11.3 MeV

x4freetext: Proton Scattering from 27Al in the Energy Range
from 3.5 to 11.3 MeV
Self-supporting aluminium targets of approximately
80 mu-g/cm2 were prepared by vacuum evaporation onto a
soluble substrate followed by stripping on a water
surface. The target thickness was obtained from the
displacement of the 874 keV resonance in
19F(p,alpha+gamma)16O when the aluminium target was
placed in front of the fluorine target.
Two silicon surface-barrier detectors were
mounted at 90. and 140. degr. to the beam direction.
